Class SerbianIDFrontSideRecognizerSettings

  • java.lang.Object

    public class SerbianIDFrontSideRecognizerSettings
extends RecognizerSettings
    Represents a settings for setting up recognizer which can scan front side of austrian national ID cards.

    • Field Detail

      • FACE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String FACE_IMAGE_NAME
        Name of the image sent to MetadataListener that contains face. This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of face image is enabled (see setReturnFacePhoto(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SIGNATURE_IMAGE_NAME

        public static final java.lang.String SIGNATURE_IMAGE_NAME

This image will be sent to MetadataListener during recognition process if displaying of signature image is enabled (see setReturnSignaturePhoto(boolean), and receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED image is enabled with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)

      • setReturnFacePhoto

        public void setReturnFacePhoto(boolean returnFacePhoto)
        Sets whether face image from ID card should be sent to MetadataListener. If enabled, image will be of type ImageType.DEWARPED, and the name of the image (see Image.getImageName()) will be equal to FACE_IMAGE_NAME, so make sure you subscribe to receiving of ImageType.DEWARPED images with MetadataSettings.ImageMetadataSettings.setDewarpedImageEnabled(boolean)
        Parameters:
        returnFacePhoto - (whether face image should be sent to MetadataListener.
